The Q3D magnetic spectrograph.
.The tritons emitted in the 118Sn(p,t)116Sn
reaction were identified by the new 1-m long focal
plane detector, consisting of a proportional counter
with cathode strip readout, designed to detect light
ions like p, d, t, 3He and alpha with a position
resolution better than 0.1 mm, good particle
identification and high count rate. The particles were
stopped in a 7-mm-thick plastic scintillator.
In the case of the 124Sn(p,t)122Sn reaction
measurements was used the 1.8-m-long focal plane
detector for light ions, consisted of an array of
single-wire proportional detectors with an additional
readout structure, followed by a rest energy plastic
scintillator detector.
.The errors in the cross sections is
